==Old English==
===Etymology===
From [[ge-|ġe-]] + ''*rōf'' ‘host, master’ (attested only in compounds: [[secgrof|secgrōf]] ‘host of men’, [[stæfrof|stæfrōf]] ‘alphabet’).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /je're:va/

===Noun===
'''ġerēfa''' ''m'' (''pl'' '''ġerēfan''')
# a [[reeve]] or official with local jurisdiction under the king; the chief magistrate of a district

===Descendents===
*English [[reeve]]

